# AI Coding Agent Rules & Hints

## Project Overview
- **Name**: Biospecimen Vue Scanner
- **Description**: A mobile-friendly browser application for scanning 96-well biospecimen plates.
- **Goal**: Facilitate fast, accurate barcode intake with visual feedback and CSV export.

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: [Vue 3](https://vuejs.org/) (Composition API, `<script setup>`)
- **Language**: [TypeScript](https://www.typescriptlang.org/)
- **Build Tool**: [Vite](https://vitejs.dev/)
- **Package Manager**: [Bun](https://bun.sh/) (Use `bun` instead of `npm` or `yarn`)
- **State Management**: [Pinia](https://pinia.vuejs.org/)
- **Icons**: [Lucide Vue Next](https://lucide.dev/guide/packages/lucide-vue-next)
- **Styling**: Vanilla CSS with a focus on modern aesthetics (glassmorphism, vibrant gradients).

## Development Guidelines

### 1. Script & Component Style
- Always use `<script setup lang="ts">`.
- Use **Composition API** exclusively.
- Prefer `ref` for simple reactive state and `reactive` for complex objects if needed, but `ref` is generally preferred for consistency.
- Keep components focused. Large components (like `App.vue`) should eventually be split into a `components/` directory.

### 2. State Management (Pinia)
- Stores are located in `src/stores/`.
- Use the **Setup Store** syntax (functions) instead of Options API.
- Maintain separate stores for distinct logic (e.g., `plateStore.ts` for plate state).

### 3. UI/UX Standards
- **Aesthetics**: Premium, modern look. Use CSS variables for colors and spacing.
- **Responsiveness**: Ensure the layout works on tablets and desktop (scanner-heavy environments).
- **Glassmorphism**: Use `.glass-panel` class for containers (semi-transparent backgrounds with backdrops-filter).
- **Animations**: Use subtle transitions and micro-animations (e.g., the pulse effect on the active well).

### 4. Workflow & Commands
- **Install Dependencies**: `bun install`
- **Run Dev Server**: `bun dev` (Runs on `http://localhost:5173`)
- **Build**: `bun run build`
- **Check Project Structure**:
  - `src/stores/`: Data logic and persistence.
  - `src/components/`: Reusable UI elements.
  - `src/assets/`: Global styles and static assets.

### 5. Coding Patterns
- **Well IDs**: Always format as Row+Column (e.g., "A1", "H12").
- **Scanning Logic**: Handle `Enter` key on inputs to trigger scan logging.
- **Directionality**: Support both Row-wise (A1 -> A2) and Column-wise (H1 -> G1) scanning.

## Instructions for AI Agents
- When adding new features, maintain the modern CSS aesthetic.
- Do not introduce new heavy dependencies without checking if existing ones (like Lucide or PapaParse) can handle it.
- Always check `src/stores/plateStore.ts` before modifying state-related logic in components.
- When generating CSS, use the existing design tokens in `src/style.css`.
